  "notes": "F1 validation of MECH-204 precision recalibration consumer under the cross-cycle persistent zero-point reference (EMA alpha=0.1). Supersedes V3-EXQ-541, which surfaced the within-cycle no-op pattern (target == rv at writeback by construction in legacy capture-only semantics). ARM_0 disables the consumer (use_rem_precision_recalibration=False); ARM_1 enables it with step=0.1 on top of the F1 substrate fix. Hazard-heavy / resource-thin env drives sustained E3 _running_variance drift between sleep cycles; the cross-cycle EMA reference now lags the moment-snapshot, so cycles 2..N have target != rv whenever drift moves rv between captures. Acceptance: C1 substrate-readiness (recalibration fires every cycle in >=2/3 ON-arm seeds), C2 movement-direction consistency with target and non-zero mean_abs_delta on cycles 2..N (>= 1e-3), C3 cross-arm divergence on post-cycle rv (>= 5%). First cycle's no-op is still expected (cold-start: persistent = first capture = rv); meaningful movement measured on cycles 2..N."
